dcterms:description: The synthetic dataset consists of time-series of two variables, one continuous (noisy sine curve) and one binary (random Bernoulli). The output is a non-linear function of the sine curve frequency and of the Bernoulli variable probability.
dcterms:title: Synthetic Dataset

dcterms:description: The Physionet dataset is a benchmark dataset from the Physionet Challenge 2012, used for predicting whether an ICU patient will survive or die during their stay at the hospital. It contains 79.75% missing values on average and is a binary classification benchmark.
dcterms:title: Physionet

dcterms:description: The Clue dataset is used to predict the discontinuation of birth control methods over time. It contains 70.29% missing values on average and requires multi-class classification.
dcterms:title: Clue
